    management: ["Follow WHO analgesic ladder for systematic pain management", "Around-the-clock (ATC) dosing for continuous pain with breakthrough doses (10-15% of 24hr total)", "Multimodal analgesia: combine opioids with non-opioids and adjuvants", "Neuropathic pain adjuvants: gabapentin, pregabalin, duloxetine, TCAs", "Bone pain: NSAIDs, bisphosphonates, radiation therapy, corticosteroids", "Non-pharmacological: positioning, massage, heat/cold, relaxation, distraction", "Reassess pain 30-60 minutes after intervention"],
    nursingActions: ["Assess pain using appropriate validated tool at regular intervals", "Administer analgesics on schedule (not PRN only for chronic pain)", "Calculate and administer breakthrough doses correctly", "Monitor for opioid side effects: sedation, respiratory depression, constipation, nausea", "Educate patient and family that adequate pain control is a right, not a privilege", "Address fears about opioid addiction (rare in palliative patients)", "Document pain assessments, interventions, and reassessments"],
